abstract: An unusual product endorsement by the president-elect adds to the company’s headaches over a politically active family member.
snippet: An unusual product endorsement by the president-elect adds to the company’s headaches over a politically active family member.
lead_paragraph: With a single tweet on Thursday, President-elect Donald J. Trump pulled L. L. Bean, the Maine retailer known for its boots, jackets and preppy New England aesthetic, back into a political crossfire.

abstract: Brooklyn on Monday waived Bennett, who is shaping up as one of the worst No. 1 picks in N.B.A. history.
snippet: Brooklyn on Monday waived Bennett, who is shaping up as one of the worst No. 1 picks in N.B.A. history.
lead_paragraph: In the final N.B.A. draft he presided over, in 2013, David Stern, then the league’s commissioner, shocked the crowd at Barclays Center when he announced that the Cleveland Cavaliers had taken Anthony Bennett with the No. 1 overall pick. A 6-foot-8 power forward who had played one year at Nevada-Las Vegas, Bennett was a surprise selection over Nerlens Noel and other top prospects.

abstract: As Donald J. Trump’s son-in-law prepares for a White House role, his undisclosed talks with a secretive Chinese company highlight potential conflicts of interest.
snippet: As Donald J. Trump’s son-in-law prepares for a White House role, his undisclosed talks with a secretive Chinese company highlight potential conflicts of interest.
lead_paragraph: On the night of Nov. 16, a group of executives gathered in a private dining room of the restaurant La Chine at the Waldorf Astoria hotel in Midtown Manhattan. The table was laden with Chinese delicacies and $2,100 bottles of Château Lafite Rothschild. At one end sat Wu Xiaohui, the chairman of the Waldorf’s owner, Anbang Insurance Group, a Chinese financial behemoth with estimated assets of $285 billion and an ownership structure shrouded in mystery. Close by sat Jared Kushner, a major New York real estate investor whose father-in-law, Donald J. Trump, had just been elected president of the United States.

abstract: With three weeks left in office, the president is using all his powers to cement his legacy and make undoing it that much harder for his successor.
snippet: With three weeks left in office, the president is using all his powers to cement his legacy and make undoing it that much harder for his successor.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Only two days after the election, President Obama sat by President-elect Donald J. Trump’s side in the Oval Office and declared that the No. 1 priority in his last days in the White House would be ensuring a smooth transition of power.

abstract: An examination of the company reveals a distinctly family business fortified with longtime loyalists that operates less on standardized procedures and more on a culture of Trump.
snippet: An examination of the company reveals a distinctly family business fortified with longtime loyalists that operates less on standardized procedures and more on a culture of Trump.
lead_paragraph: When Tiah Joo Kim arrived at the Manhattan headquarters of the Trump Organization to pitch a hotel and condominium project in Vancouver, British Columbia, he expected the famous company with ventures across the globe to come with capacious offices and a staff of hundreds. Instead, he was led through a mere two floors with what appeared to be no more than a few dozen employees. “Lean,” Mr. Tiah, a young Malaysian developer, remembers thinking as he walked the halls.

abstract: Kellyanne Conway, who served as campaign manager, will become highest-ranking woman on Donald Trump’s staff, with frequent access to the president.
snippet: Kellyanne Conway, who served as campaign manager, will become highest-ranking woman on Donald Trump’s staff, with frequent access to the president.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — Kellyanne Conway, the Republican pollster and strategist who helped guide Donald J. Trump to victory in November, on Thursday was appointed counselor to the president, becoming the highest-ranking woman at the White House and one of his principal messengers to the public.

headline_main: What’s on TV Tuesday: ‘Tony Bennett Celebrates 90’ and ‘The Year: 2016’

abstract: For the 35th anniversary of the hit musical’s Broadway opening, Sheryl Lee Ralph and Ben Harney look back on a “dream come true” and its aftermath.
snippet: For the 35th anniversary of the hit musical’s Broadway opening, Sheryl Lee Ralph and Ben Harney look back on a “dream come true” and its aftermath.
lead_paragraph: On Dec. 20, 1981, “Dreamgirls’’ opened at the Imperial Theater, bringing a “seismic emotional jolt” to Broadway, as the critic Frank Rich wrote in The New York Times. Written by Henry Krieger and Tom Eyen and directed by Michael Bennett, the musical followed the path of a Supremes-style girl group and its driven, unscrupulous manager.
